Usage: lxa [OPTIONS] [PATH...]
       lxa inspect [PATH...]

lxa is a Linux-first file listing tool focused on extended attributes and XDG metadata.

Options:
  -v, --version                  Show lxa version
  -m, --format string            Format (used to be mode, now commas)
  -R, --recursive                Traverse directories recursively
  -f, --filter string            Apply filter expression (also used for not sort and hidden)
  -j, --json                     Output in JSON format
  -H, --dereference-command-line Follow symlinks on command line
  -l                             Long listing format
  -o                             Long listing without group information
  -g                             Long listing without user information
  -a, --all                      Include hidden files
  -A, --almost-all               Do not list implied . and ..
  -b, --escape                   Print C-style escapes for nongraphic characters
      --block-size=SIZE          Scale sizes by SIZE
  -B, --ignore-backups           Do not list implied entries ending with ~
  -c                             Sort by ctime
  -d, --directory                List directories themselves
  -D, --dired                    Generate output designed for Emacs' dired mode
  -F, --classify[=WHEN]          Append indicator
      --file-type                Likewise, except do not append '*'
      --format=WORD              across -x, commas -m, long -l, single-column -1
      --full-time                Like -l --time-style=full-iso
      --group-directories-first  Group directories before files
  -G, --no-group                 In a long listing, don't print group names
  -h, --human-readable           Print sizes in human readable format
      --si                       Likewise, but use powers of 1000 not 1024
      --dereference-command-line-symlink-to-dir
      --hide=PATTERN             Do not list implied entries matching shell PATTERN
      --hyperlink[=WHEN]         Hyperlink file names WHEN
      --indicator-style=WORD     Append indicator with style WORD
  -i, --inode                    Print the index number of each file
  -I, --ignore=PATTERN           Do not list implied entries matching shell PATTERN
  -k, --kibibytes                Default to 1024-byte blocks for file system usage
  -L, --dereference              When showing file info for symlink, show referenced file
  -n, --numeric-uid-gid          List numeric user and group IDs
  -N, --literal                  Print entry names without quoting
  -p, --indicator-style=slash    Append / indicator to directories
  -q, --hide-control-chars       Print ? instead of nongraphic characters
      --show-control-chars       Show nongraphic characters as-is
  -Q, --quote-name               Enclose entry names in double quotes
      --quoting-style=WORD       Use quoting style WORD
  -r, --reverse                  Reverse order while sorting
  -s, --size                     Print the allocated size of each file
  -S                             Sort by file size
      --sort=WORD                Sort by: name, size, time, version, extension
      --time=WORD                Select which timestamp used to display or sort
      --time-style=TIME_STYLE    Time/date format with -l
  -t                             Sort by time, newest first
  -T, --tabsize=COLS             Assume tab stops at each COLS
  -u                             Sort by, and show, access time
  -U                             Do not sort directory entries
  -v                             Natural sort of (version) numbers
  -w, --width=COLS               Set output width to COLS
  -x                             List entries by lines instead of by columns
  -X                             Sort alphabetically by entry extension
  -Z, --context                  Print any security context of each file
      --zero                     End each output line with NUL
      --header                   Show header row (title)
      --author                   Show author (user.author)
      --creator                  Show creator (user.creator)
      --origin                   Show origin (user.origin)
      --checksum                 Show checksum (user.checksum)
      --selinux                  Show SELinux context
      --samba                    Show Samba DOS attributes
      --capabilities             Show Capabilities
      --acl                      Show ACL presence
  -W, --max-tags-width int       Maximum display width for tags (default 40)
  -C                             Multi-column layout, or maximum display width for comments
  -1                             Single column layout

Mutation Options:
  --set-tags=...                 Set user.xdg.tags (comma-separated)
  --add-tags=...                 Add tags without duplicates
  --remove-tags=...              Remove specified tags
  --clear-tags                   Remove user.xdg.tags entirely
  --set-comment=...              Set user.xdg.comment
  --clear-comment                Remove user.xdg.comment entirely
  --set-rating=...               Set user.xdg.rating
  --clear-rating                 Remove user.xdg.rating entirely

Inspect Options:
  -X, --all-xdg                  Show all XDG metadata attributes
  -A, --all-xattr                Show all xattrs
